Skip entity types without a views base table in xmlsitemap_views_data_alter().

getBaseTable() returns NULL for config (and some other) entity types. Using
that NULL value as an array offset triggers a runtime deprecation as of
PHP 8.4 ("Using null as an array offset is deprecated"). Capture the base
table once and continue when it is empty before using it as an array key.

No upstream issue covers this runtime deprecation (drupal.org #3499531 only
fixes implicitly-nullable function parameters), so this is a self-rolled patch.

diff --git a/xmlsitemap.views.inc b/xmlsitemap.views.inc
index 6a90675..85c6de3 100644
--- a/xmlsitemap.views.inc
+++ b/xmlsitemap.views.inc
@@ -71,10 +71,17 @@ function xmlsitemap_views_data() {
  */
 function xmlsitemap_views_data_alter(array &$data) {
   foreach (\Drupal::entityTypeManager()->getDefinitions() as $id => $definition) {
-    if (!xmlsitemap_link_entity_check_enabled($id) && !empty($data[$definition->getBaseTable()])) {
+    // Config entity types (and some others) have no views base table, in which
+    // case getBaseTable() returns NULL. Skip them: using NULL as an array
+    // offset is deprecated as of PHP 8.4 and there is nothing to alter anyway.
+    $base_table = $definition->getBaseTable();
+    if (empty($base_table)) {
       continue;
     }
-    $data[$definition->getBaseTable()]['xmlsitemap_settings'] = [
+    if (!xmlsitemap_link_entity_check_enabled($id) && !empty($data[$base_table])) {
+      continue;
+    }
+    $data[$base_table]['xmlsitemap_settings'] = [
       'title' => t('XML Sitemap Settings'),
       'relationship' => [
         'id' => 'standard',
